11/08/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Danish diplomat Soren Jessen-Petersen, the new UNMIK chief, is due to arrive in the province on 16 August, a UN spokesman said Tuesday (10 August). Jessen-Petersen "will approach this challenge determined to move the agenda forward, in the interests of all communities in Kosovo and in the interest of peace and stability in the entire region", the spokesman said. The diplomat will spend his first days in the province meeting with government and ethnic community leaders. Jessen-Petersen succeeds Finnish diplomat Harri Holkeri, who resigned citing health problems. (AFP, BETA, Tanjug, HINA - 10/08/04)
